# Module Architecture

## Structure

```
web/                    Frontend (React, client-side)
  components/           UI components
    ai/                 Chatbot components
    filters/            Filter sidebar components
  contexts/             React contexts (cart, etc.)
  hooks/                Custom React hooks

api/                    Backend (server-side business logic)
  services/             Business logic (stateless, testable)
    reservation.ts      Booking flow orchestration
    qr-code.ts          QR assignment + validation
    esim.ts             BNESIM provisioning
    email-triggers.ts   Domain events → email bridge

shared/                 Cross-cutting (used by both web & api)
  config/               Client configs (stripe, supabase)
  emails/               Email system (templates, sender, components)
  types/                TypeScript types
  validations/          Zod schemas
  offers.ts             Product offers data
  products.ts           Product catalog data

app/                    Next.js routing layer (THIN)
  api/                  API routes → validate + call service + respond
  (client)/             Client grouped pages
  paiement/             Checkout flow
```

## Import Aliases (tsconfig.json)

```
@web/*     → ./web/*
@api/*     → ./api/*
@shared/*  → ./shared/*
@/*        → ./*  (legacy fallback)
```

## Rules

1. **app/ is thin** — validate input, call service, return response
2. **api/services/ owns logic** — no Request/Response inside services
3. **shared/ is infrastructure** — configs, types, utilities, emails
4. **web/ is frontend** — components, hooks, contexts
5. **No circular deps** — web can import shared, api can import shared, neither imports each other
6. **Barrel exports** for modules with 3+ files (index.ts)

## Import Direction

```
app/ ──→ @web/* (pages import components)
app/ ──→ @api/* (api routes import services)
app/ ──→ @shared/* (both can use shared)
api/ ──→ @shared/* (services use configs, types, emails)
web/ ──→ @shared/* (components use types, products)
web/ ✗─→ @api/*  (NEVER import backend in frontend)
api/ ✗─→ @web/*  (NEVER import frontend in backend)
```

## Adding a New Feature

1. Needs a page? → `app/(client)/` or `app/(admin)/`
2. Needs an API? → `app/api/feature/route.ts` (thin)
3. Has business logic? → `api/services/feature.ts`
4. Needs shared types? → `shared/types/`
5. Needs validation? → `shared/validations/`
6. Needs config? → `shared/config/`
7. Needs UI? → `web/components/feature/`
